{"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StateManagement","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ThemingGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/FocusSystem","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/StatusBarGuide","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/AppearanceAndColors","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/CustomViews","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/KeyboardShortcuts","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PaletteReference","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/ListAndTable","doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/LayoutSystem"],"generated":true,"title":"Guides","anchor":"Guides"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit’s preference system enables "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"bottom-up data flow"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the reverse of environment values. While the environment passes data down from parent to child, preferences let child views publish values that ancestors can observe and react to."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The system mirrors SwiftUI’s preference API and consists of three parts:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PreferenceKey","isActive":true}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Protocol that defines a named value type with a default and a reduce strategy","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/PreferenceValues","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"type":"text","text":": Type-safe storage that holds all preference values for a scope"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PreferenceStorage"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Stack-based collector that manages preference contexts per render pass"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A built-in example is ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey"},{"text":": a child view sets ","type":"text"},{"code":".navigationTitle(\"Settings\")","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and the enclosing navigation container reads that preference to render the title bar.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Defining-a-Preference-Key","text":"Defining a Preference Key"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A preference key declares what type of value it carries and how multiple values from sibling children are combined:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct CounterKey: PreferenceKey {","    static let defaultValue: Int = 0","","    static func reduce(value: inout Int, nextValue: () -> Int) {","        value += nextValue()","    }","}"]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"defaultValue"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Returned when no child has set this preference","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"reduce(value:nextValue:)","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":": Combines values when multiple children set the same key","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation simply takes the last value. Override it when you need additive behavior (summing counts), array collection, or other merge strategies."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Setting-a-Preference","text":"Setting a Preference"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Child views publish a preference using the ","type":"text"},{"code":".preference(key:value:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" modifier:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct ItemView: View {","    var body: some View {","        Text(\"Item\")","            .preference(key: CounterKey.self, value: 1)","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Under the hood, this wraps the view in a ","type":"text"},{"code":"PreferenceModifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"preferences.setValue(_:forKey:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" during rendering. The value is reduced into the current scope using the key’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"reduce","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Observing-Preferences","text":"Observing Preferences"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ancestor views react to collected preferences using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".onPreferenceChange(_:perform:)"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct ItemList: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","            ItemView()","        }","        .onPreferenceChange(CounterKey.self) { totalCount in","            \/\/ totalCount == 3 (three children each set value: 1, additive reduce)","        }","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The modifier pushes a new preference context, renders all children (which set their preferences), pops the context, and fires the callback with the accumulated result.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"The-Navigation-Title-Shortcut","text":"The Navigation Title Shortcut"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit provides "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/NavigationTitleKey","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a built-in preference key with a convenience modifier:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct SettingsPage: View {","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Text(\"App settings go here\")","        }","        .navigationTitle(\"Settings\")","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NavigationTitleKey"},{"text":" uses the default ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"reduce"},{"text":" (last value wins), so the deepest child’s title takes precedence.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"How-Preferences-Flow-per-Frame","text":"How Preferences Flow per Frame"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Preferences are collected fresh every frame. Here’s the lifecycle within a single render pass:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Reset","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"code":"RenderLoop.render()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" calls ","type":"text"},{"code":"preferences.beginRenderPass()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", clearing all callbacks and resetting the stack to a single empty context","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set","type":"text"}]},{"text":": As the view tree renders top-down, ","type":"text"},{"code":"PreferenceModifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" views call ","type":"text"},{"code":"setValue(_:forKey:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which reduces values into the current stack frame","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Scope","type":"text"}]},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OnPreferenceChangeModifier"},{"text":" pushes a new context before rendering its subtree, isolating child preferences","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineC